parameters:
\EMP What do you want? I'm busy. If you don't have
any business, then get out.

\n<Town Mayor>What are you doing? What do you intend to do by
taking away my time without permission?

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I apologize for the sudden visit. I am Rain, a
holy knight dispatched from the capital.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>I apologize for the urgency, but I will need to
take some of your time.

\n<Town Mayor>Well, fine. I'll listen to what you have to say,
considering you're a knight. What do you need?

\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>You may not be aware of some things, but first let
me talk about what is happening in this town.

Rain explained the events leading up to now to the
town mayor.

\n<Town Mayor>Geez, you sure talk a lot. \.So? What do you
want me to do?

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I would like to borrow the key to unlock the seal
of the dungeon that the town mayor inherited from
their predecessor.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>If we have the key, I can immediately go and
investigate to confirm the presence of the magical
device.

\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>Indeed, I do have the key... \., but this story
about demons and amplification of desires sounds
suspicious.

\n<Town Mayor>Including the time when I was assisting my father,
who was the previous town mayor, I have been
observing this town for over 10 years. However, I
don't see any particular abnormalities in the
current situation.

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>However, it is true that there has been an
increase in crime and monsters.
\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>Isn't that just a passing thing?

\n<Town Mayor>And even if your story is true, that key is from
several decades ago. I only inherited it from my
father and have only seen it once. I've never
touched it.

\n<Town Mayor>If something were to happen as a result of using
such a thing, can you take responsibility? Can you
swear that you won't cause any trouble for me?

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>That... this could become a major event for this
town, no, for this country!

\n<Town Mayor>Hmph, don't go barking like a knight. Consider my
position for a moment.

\n<Town Mayor>If you want to move me, the mayor of this town,
then you will bear any responsibility. \.Even
though you are a holy knight, I cannot believe the
words of a mere soldier.

\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(I see... I heard that \. had a strong
personality, but... to be honest, they're a real
pain in the ass.)

\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(But I can't back down here... *sigh* From what I
saw at the coast, the only place that seems to
have a device is the dungeon. The key is
absolutely necessary...)

\CE[78]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(I don't want to, but I have to do something here,
even if it's a bit clumsy...)

\OC[31]\N<Rain>If things continue like this, this town will truly
be in a dire situation...! Town Mayor, you might
also end up being used as a pawn by the demons...!

\n<Town Mayor>Hmmm... If that's the case, then show me your
determination.

\n<Town Mayor>Ah, so you really want the key, huh? If that's the
case, are you willing to do anything for it?

\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>You have a good appearance. Even compared to our
maids, you're quite exceptional.

\n<Town Mayor>I like beautiful women. So, why don't you serve me
as a maid? If you can satisfy me, I'll give you
the key.

\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(This person... is the worst. Probably, they're
consumed by greed, unrelated to Nightmare
Heaven...

\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(Honestly, considering the current situation, I
think I can contact the capital and request a
royal decree... \. However, it will take too much
time for the messenger to arrive, and it would be
foolish to expose incompetence by resorting to
such measures...)

\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(My incompetence will lower the evaluation of my
superior, Jazz...! I must avoid that at all
costs...!)

\CE[77]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(If it can be resolved with my body... I can offer
my services once or twice...! \. I can't hesitate
when it comes to something lewd...

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>... In exchange for borrowing the key, please
let me serve you...

\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>Oh, I see. So you're showing me your
determination! How interesting.

\n<Town Mayor>If your service can satisfy me, I'll give you the
key. Just do your best.
\n<Town Mayor>Once you change into this, come to my bedroom.

\n<Town Mayor>If you want, you can stop now and run away. I'll
give you those clothes, so whenever you feel like
serving, come wearing them. Fufufu.

\n<Town Mayor>Hmmm, the size fits well. How about becoming my
maid?

\n<Town Mayor>Hey, what's with that attitude? Is that how you
speak to someone who is here to serve? Do you
understand the meaning of service?

\CE[79]\CE[78]\n<Town Mayor>That's right, be careful. Even though it's only
for the duration of this transaction, you are in a
position to serve me. It's unthinkable to offer
reluctant and sulky services.

\n<Town Mayor>Well, since this is your first time being a maid,
I'll make it easier for you to be conscious of
your role. Call me 'Master' when referring to me.
Understand?

\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>Alright, then show me. Show me your 'service',
now.

\n<Town Mayor>That was quite a good service. Perhaps you're more
suited for this than swinging a sword, don't you
think?

\n<Town Mayor>If you're in need of money, it would be good to
come and earn it at my place. Of course, as a
maid, you'll have to put your body on the line.
Fufufu...

\C[17] I became able to work at the Town Mayor's
mansion.

\CE[77]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(...If I break here, I feel like I'll lose
something important...)
\CE[78]\CE[84]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(I can't... I can't give in here!

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I only serve those I must protect! Absolutely not
you!

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Moreover, you have insulted me, a holy knight
chosen by the king who wields a single sword, and
even hindered my missions from the country for
your own desires. This is an act that deserves
sufficient punishment.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>If you continue to refuse cooperation, then
there's no other choice. You will receive the
appropriate judgment and as a royal decree, I will
take custody of the key!

\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>Alright, alright, stop shouting. Geez, what a
worthless person to deal with...

Do you really have the time to go through the
trouble of issuing a royal decree?

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>...Indeed, that is true. But if you refuse to
lend me the key, then there is no other choice...!

\n<Town Mayor>Well, I suppose there's no other choice. I'll give
in. \. I'll sell you the key.
\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Sell...? Do you mean to let go of it?

\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>Ah, as long as I am the owner of the key, there
will inevitably be some responsibility attached to
it.

\n<Town Mayor>In that case, why don't you just buy it? I'm not
particularly attached to the key, you know.

\CE[79]\n<Town Mayor>\C[17]160000\G\C[0], there's no room for
negotiation. However, well, it would be a large
sum of money for a single soldier. If you want, I
can let you earn it here.

\n<Town Mayor>Only speak to me when you have the money \C[17]or
when you want to earn it\C[0]. Don't bother me for
anything else.
I am now able to work at the Town Mayor's mansion.
'Buy the key from the mayor for 160,000 gems'

\n<Town Mayor>Are you prepared for \C[17]160000\G\C[0]? Or do
you want to earn some money?

\n<Town Mayor>You're still lacking. Don't speak until you can
come up with the money.

\CE[79]\CE[84]\n<Town Mayor>Hmph, fine. It's a much smarter choice than
toiling away in this town. I hope you'll work up a
sweat for my sake.
\CE[84]\n<Town Mayor>There's no more work for today. Go home.

\n<Town Mayor>Don't talk to me unless you have \C[17]money
ready\C[0] or you want to earn \C[17]money\C[0].
\n<Town Mayor>Now, this is the promised 'key.' Take it.

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I can definitely feel the same magic as the
dungeon gate. There's no mistake about it.

\n<Town Mayor>Now, this key is yours. I don't care what happens
next. Do as you please.
\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Yes... I will do as you say.
\n<Town Mayor>Oh, have you come to make some money?

\n<Town Mayor>Very well. Today, too, you shall sweat for my
sake.

\n<Town Mayor>So, what are you going to do? Make up your mind
quickly.
\n<Town Mayor>I'm busy. If you don't have any business, get out.

\n<Town Mayor>There's no more work today. If you want to earn
money, come back tomorrow.

\EMP Something sparkly doesn't happen in two
places at the same time, so be careful

\EMP Once you clean up 10 places, you'll find
another 10 places full of trash!

\EMP Master doesn't pay attention to the details,
so honestly, everyone isn't really working much.

\EMP My master may have a terrible personality,
but they're skilled in bed...

\n<Town Mayor>Hmm? What's wrong, your hands stopped? Work
properly!

\n<Town Mayor>Come on, focus. Don't stop your hands for every
little thing.

\n<Town Mayor>Hmm, it seems you're taking good care of yourself.
Hehehe...
